    {
      "id": "ee121a23-dd45-477e-9833-0bd52ee5f677",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$Q(z)=z^2+40z-300$.\r\n$$\\begin{array}{c|ccc}\r\n &1&40&-300\\\\ \\hline \\textrm{facteur }6&1&46&-24\\\\\r\n &1&52&\\\\ &1&&\r\n\\end{array}$$\r\nDonc, $Q(6+u)=u^2+52u-24$. Par conséquent,\r\n$R(v):=100Q(6+v/10)=v^2+520u-2400$.\r\nComme $2400/520\\sim 5$, on trouve $R(5)>0$ et $R(4)<0$.\r\nDonc $$2,64<\\sqrt{7}<2.65.$$",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q(z)=z^2+40z-300\\)</span>. <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{array}{c|ccc}\n&amp;1&amp;40&amp;-300\\\\ \\hline \\textrm{facteur\n}6&amp;1&amp;46&amp;-24\\\\\n&amp;1&amp;52&amp;\\\\ &amp;1&amp;&amp;\n\\end{array}\\]</span> Donc, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Q(6+u)=u^2+52u-24\\)</span>. Par conséquent, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(R(v):=100Q(6+v/10)=v^2+520u-2400\\)</span>. Comme\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(2400/520\\sim 5\\)</span>, on trouve <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(R(5)&gt;0\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(R(4)&lt;0\\)</span>. Donc <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[2,64&lt;\\sqrt{7}&lt;2.65.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
